casebody.data:
COATES v. WALTERS. No. 339,

Misc.

Decided November 6, 1961. Vito J. Cassan for appellant. Louis J. Lefkowitz, Attorney General of New York, Paxton Blair, Solicitor General, and Jean M. Coon, Assistant Attorney General, for appellee. Per Curiam.

The motion to dismiss is granted and the appeal is dismissed for want of a substantial federal question.
